text: Rosemary M Morgan (born 1941), is a female former athlete who competed for England. ==Athletics career== She represented England and won a silver medal in the javelin at the 1962 British Empire and Commonwealth Games in Perth, Western Australia. She was a member of the Ilford Athletic Club. ==References== Category:1941 births Category:English female javelin throwers Category:Commonwealth Games medallists in athletics Category:Commonwealth Games silver medallists for England Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1962 British Empire and Commonwealth Games Category:Living people
